get_data_pool_info(uint64,bytes32).details: get data pool information in epoch `epoch`

params._data_pool: the data pool uid you want to check
params._epoch: the epoch you want to checkout

params._amount: the amount of attestations created by one user
params._data_pool: the data pool to be searched
params._total: the amount of attestations created all users

set_data_pools(bytes32,uint64,uint64,uin.details: Only admin can call this function and only current epoch or the epoch in future can be set. So to include the attestation before airdrop stage start, the data pool info in epoch 0 should be set before AirdropMiner starts.

params._epoch: epoch in which reward of data pool is `_reward`
params._reward: reward of data pool in epoch `_epoch`
params._s: window size of data pool information
params._t1: denominator of step in data pool
params._t2: moleculestep of step in data pool

set_epoch(uint64).details: Only airdrop minter can call this function

set_gauge_controller(address).details: Only callable once, when gauge controller has not yet been set

set_minter(address).details: Only callable once, when minter has not yet been set

update_each_epoch_attestations(bytes32[].details: Only admin can call this function

user_extractable_reward(address,bytes32[.details: Only airdrop minter can call this function

params._addr: the address you want to checkout the extractable

params.data_pools: the slice of data pools that are searched

get_rate_of_pool(uint64,uint64,bytes32,u.notice: Get how many reward user can get under `_amount`

get_total_attestations(uint64,bytes32).notice: Get total attestation amount in `_data_pool` in epoch `_epoch`

set_data_pools(bytes32,uint64,uint64,uin.notice: Add or Set new data pool info.

update_each_epoch_attestations(bytes32[].notice: Update total generated attestations amount in each epoch

user_extractable_reward(address,bytes32[.notice: Get how much reward _addr can extract according to the given info and when the user extract reward successfully,log of extracting reward should be recorded.
